BEJI CAID ESSEBSI promised to fix the economy, re-establish security and consolidate Tunisia’s democracy—but all of that remains unresolved as the country begins its search for a new leader. Pet ownership is surging around the world, as are ways to pamper pets. Who owns whom here? And, homeopathy gets diluted as France removes its state subsidy for the pseudoscience. Runtime: 21 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn